{"id":"news-no-sr-llm-primary-fallback","input":"今天有什么 AI 新闻","expected":{"web":"optional","executor":"tool_using"},"comment":"P5-2/P5-4: LLM is the primary classifier. When SR is not invoked (no decision, no rejection) the deterministic baseline is `optional`, not `forbidden`. routing_status=sr_not_invoked makes this observable; executor-resolver Rule 5 (degraded+optional) keeps the task on tool_using. Pre-P5 this used to fall to forbidden+fast as a 'conservative fallback', which silently turned ambiguous research-class queries into fast hallucinations + truthfulness refusals. The LLM-primary fix is to default to a tool-capable executor — when no web tool is configured, the LLM just answers honestly without claiming a search."}
